# AKOS Synthesis Before Tranche

Use this rule whenever **a tranche of work approaches commit-time** —
a wave that closes; a kit that ships; an engagement phase that commits;
a canonical CSV that mints; a brand surface that deploys; an external
deliverable that ships. Codifies operator decisions **D-IH-86-EA**
(doctrine mint + INFO ramp), **D-IH-86-EB** (10-dimension probe set
ratification), **D-IH-86-EC** (5-option disposition enum + per-tranche-
class dimension firing rules), **D-IH-86-ED** (INFO→FAIL ramp posture
+ broad-fire cadence), and **D-IH-86-EE** (paired SOP+runbook gate per
`akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc` Rule 1; ratified at this rule's
mint commit). Mechanical companion to
[`SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md).

This rule does **not** define the doctrine — that lives in the canonical.
This rule names the mechanical bar future agents and operators inherit
by default when authoring any tranche-class artifact.

## When this rule applies

A tranche workflow is in scope for this rule when **any** of:

- The tranche is one of the 6 tranche classes: **engagement**,
  **specialty_mint**, **internal_governance** (with non-J-OP audience
  OR ≥ 3 files), **canonical_csv_mint**, **brand_surface**,
  **external_deliverable**.
- The tranche ships ≥ 5 files in one commit OR touches a canonical
  CSV.
- The tranche carries a `tranche_class:` frontmatter tag in a
  master-roadmap, candidate, or `.tranche-charter.md` file.
- A wave-charter or wave-close commit introduces a new tranche-class.
- An engagement charters or commits a phase.
- A specialty canonical mints (every specialty mint is a
  specialty_mint-class tranche; this rule's own mint is the recursive
  worked example).
- A brand surface deploys (web page, deck slide, dossier render).
- An external deliverable ships (investor dossier, ENISA evidence,
  advisor handoff pack).
- The operator explicitly requests a synthesis pass (on_demand
  cadence).

Out of scope (per `SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md` §9):

- Chore-only commits (typo fixes, link-rot fixes, formatting,
  CHANGELOG-only edits).
- Per-engagement WIP synthesis under `docs/wip/intelligence/`
  (governed by brand-baseline-reality + per-engagement counterparty
  brief disciplines, not this one).
- Internal helper modules with no audience/channel/scenario impact.
- Pre-2026-05-25 tranches that have already shipped (the discipline
  is forward-only from this mint commit, not retroactive).

## RULE 1 — Run the synthesis sweep BEFORE the tranche commits (binding)

Every in-scope tranche MUST execute the 10-dimension synthesis sweep
BEFORE the tranche's atomic commit lands. The sweep output
(`docs/wip/planning/<parent-initiative>/reports/synthesis-<tranche-id>-<YYYY-MM-DD>.md`)
is a `§3 mechanical-evidence` row in the tranche's UAT report OR an
`§N synthesis` section in the tranche's master-roadmap when no UAT
report applies.

Pre-tranche temporal posture is the load-bearing claim: this rule's
sister disciplines INDEX_INTEGRITY + INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION both run
AFTER commit (wave-close cadence); SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE runs
BEFORE commit (tranche-charter cadence). Composing the three covers
the full work-lifecycle cadence — design-layer review (this rule),
execution-layer regression (INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION), and index-layer
freshness (INDEX_INTEGRITY).

The 10 dimensions are defined in
[`SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md)
§2. Summary:

| # | Dimension | Probe question | Severity |
|:--|:---|:---|:---|
| 1 | SYN-01-AUDIENCE-COMPLETENESS | Has every audience class touched by the tranche been named? | judgement (WARN ramp; FAIL when empty for non-internal_governance) |
| 2 | SYN-02-CHANNEL-COVERAGE | Has every channel through which the output reaches each audience been named? | judgement (WARN ramp) |
| 3 | SYN-03-SCENARIO-INVENTORY | Have all scenarios the audience-channel pairs will be in when consuming the output been named? | judgement (WARN ramp) |
| 4 | SYN-04-BRAND-REGISTER-CITATION | Has the tranche cited which brand register applies per audience? (internal CORPINT vs translated-external) | **mandatory-citation** (FAIL ramp) |
| 5 | SYN-05-GOVERNANCE-RATIFICATION-LINEAGE | Has the tranche cited which D-IH-NN-X decisions ratify the design intent? | **mandatory-citation** (FAIL ramp) |
| 6 | SYN-06-ERP-SURFACE-CITATION | For engagement-class tranches: has the tranche named which of the 3 ERP-engagement-governance surfaces it lives in? (operator dashboard / customer dashboard / ERP workflow join) | judgement (WARN ramp; conditional on engagement class per §11) |
| 7 | SYN-07-TRANCHE-ATOMICITY | Is the tranche scoped as ONE atomic commit (or one operator-readable artifact)? | **atomicity binary** (FAIL ramp) |
| 8 | SYN-08-REVERSIBILITY-DECLARATION | Has the tranche declared its reversibility class (low / medium / high) with rationale? | **mandatory-citation** (FAIL ramp) |
| 9 | SYN-09-CLOSING-LOOP-TEST | Has the tranche named the self-test / field-test / observability signal that confirms the tranche works as designed post-ship? | judgement (WARN ramp) |
| 10 | SYN-10-RECIPIENT-FALLBACK-CHANNEL | Has the tranche named the traditional-means fallback for recipients who don't access the primary surface? *"even if they don't log so much or see it that much"* | judgement (WARN ramp) |

Per-tranche-class fire-set rules are encoded in `DIMENSION_FIRE_RULES`
in [`akos/hlk_synthesis_before_tranche.py`](../../akos/hlk_synthesis_before_tranche.py)
and locked under `resolve_fire_set(tranche_class, conditional_triggers)`
helper:

| Tranche class | Always-fire | Conditional |
|:---|:---|:---|
| **engagement** | all 10 | none |
| **specialty_mint** | 7 (SYN-01/02/04/05/07/08/09) | SYN-03 (when end-user scenarios) |
| **internal_governance** | 3 (SYN-05/07/08) | SYN-01/02/04/09 (when non-J-OP audience) |
| **canonical_csv_mint** | 6 (SYN-01/04/05/07/08/09) | SYN-02/03/10 (when CSV surfaces in dashboards) |
| **brand_surface** | 9 (all except SYN-06) | SYN-06 (when engagement-scoped) |
| **external_deliverable** | all 10 | none |

## RULE 2 — Findings disposition via inline-ratify 5-option enum (binding)

Every WARN or FAIL finding from the sweep MUST be dispositioned via
an inline `AskQuestion` gate per
[`akos-inline-ratification.mdc`](akos-inline-ratification.mdc) + the
paired [`inline-ratify-craft`](../skills/inline-ratify-craft/SKILL.md)
skill, using the 5-option enum codified in
[`SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md)
§6 + ratified at `D-IH-86-EC`:

1. **scope-complete** (default for WARN findings on always-fire dims
   when the operator's prior framing makes the missing scope load-
   bearing) — extend the tranche scope to include the missing
   dimension; re-run the sweep; commit when clean.
2. **scope-extend** (default for WARN findings on conditional dims
   when adding to this tranche would over-burden it) — file an
   OPS_REGISTER row or a forward-charter pointer; commit THIS tranche
   as-is with the scope-extension explicitly named in the synthesis
   report.
3. **scope-narrow** (default for FAIL findings on SYN-07 atomicity
   when the tranche is non-atomic) — narrow the tranche's scope to
   the synthesis-validated minimum; defer removed scope to a follow-
   up tranche.
4. **defer-OPS** (default for INFO findings) — low-priority gap that
   defers indefinitely with a tracker row.
5. **escalate-to-blocker-tracker** (when operator-time exceeds the
   inline-ratify window) — mint
   `docs/wip/planning/_blockers/<slug>-tracker.md` per
   [`akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc`](akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc).

When findings exceed 10, split the gates into 2 `AskQuestion` batches
(per inline-ratify-craft Principle 5 batching guidance). When findings
exceed 20, halt and propose splitting the tranche into Tranche-N +
Tranche-N.5 (the bandwidth recovery pattern proven at INTER_WAVE_REGRESSION
Wave M.5 precedent).

Time-box recovery: 24h+ operator silence + clean validators + reversible
dispositions auto-default to the recommended option per
`akos-inline-ratification.mdc` Time-box section. Irreversible
dispositions (`scope-narrow` on a tranche that already shipped a partial;
commercial-share decisions; brand-canon edits with sibling-repo carry-
overs) NEVER auto-default — halt and escalate per
[`akos-governance-remediation.mdc`](akos-governance-remediation.mdc).

## RULE 3 — Run the runbook self-test at every pre_commit (binding)

The runbook
[`scripts/synthesis_before_tranche_check.py --self-test`](../../scripts/synthesis_before_tranche_check.py)
+ the validator
[`scripts/validate_synthesis_before_tranche.py --self-test`](../../scripts/validate_synthesis_before_tranche.py)
verify the chassis (10-probe dispatch coverage + Pydantic fixtures +
fire-rule invariants + enum cardinality) at every
`py scripts/verify.py pre_commit` invocation via:

- [`config/verification-profiles.json`](../../config/verification-profiles.json)
  `pre_commit.steps`:
  `validate_synthesis_before_tranche_self_test` +
  `synthesis_before_tranche_check_self_test`.
- [`scripts/release-gate.py`](../../scripts/release-gate.py):
  `run_synthesis_before_tranche_self_test` +
  `run_synthesis_before_tranche_check_self_test`.

The self-test cost is ~3s combined (Pydantic instantiation + helper
spot-checks; no real tranche-scope drift evaluation). The full per-
tranche sweep (the runbook without `--self-test`) runs at
tranche-charter cadence only — NOT at every pre_commit (which would
be too expensive AND would conflate with sister disciplines'
post-commit sweeps).

Per `D-IH-86-ED` INFO → FAIL ramp:

- Wave R+1 P3 Commit 2b (mint): self-test PASS at pre_commit; full
  sweep runs once for the first worked example (this canonical's own
  mint).
- Wave R+1 P3 + Wave S: full sweep runs at each in-scope tranche;
  self-test stays PASS.
- Promotion to FAIL: per RULE 5 below + `SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md`
  §5 Stage 2 gate.

## RULE 4 — Paired SOP+runbook contract honored (binding per D-IH-86-EE)

Every executable invocation of this discipline must respect the AC-
HUMAN + AC-AUTOMATION pairing per
[`akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc`](akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc)
Rule 1:

- **AC-HUMAN** — a human OR an AIC role_owner (PMO interim; COO when
  activated per I76) can run the synthesis sweep + dispose findings
  following
  [`SOP-PEOPLE_SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_001.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/SOP-PEOPLE_SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_001.md)
  without invoking the runbook (the SOP walks the 10 questions one
  by one with worked examples).
- **AC-AUTOMATION** — the runbook
  [`scripts/synthesis_before_tranche_check.py`](../../scripts/synthesis_before_tranche_check.py)
  fires unattended at:
  (a) `--self-test` mode in pre_commit + release-gate (always);
  (b) `--check-charter <path>` mode when a tranche-charter file
  exists and the operator (or AIC) invokes the runbook explicitly;
  (c) `--tranche-id <slug> --tranche-class <class> [--audiences ...]
  [--ratifying-decisions ...] [--reversibility ...] [--closing-loop-
  test ...]` inline-CLI mode for ad-hoc sweeps without a charter file.

Both surfaces are SSOT for the same process; neither supersedes the
other. The `process_list.csv` row
`hol_peopl_dtp_synthesis_before_tranche_001` (lands at Commit 2c-b)
formally binds the pairing per `akos-executable-process-catalog.mdc`
Rule 1.

## RULE 5 — INFO → FAIL ramp gated on 3-worked-example threshold (binding)

The validator + runbook self-test launch at INFO at this rule's mint
commit. Promotion to FAIL requires (Stage 2 gate per
[`SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/People/canonicals/SYNTHESIS_BEFORE_TRANCHE_DISCIPLINE.md)
§5):

1. ≥ 3 worked examples applied the discipline cleanly:
   (i) **this canonical's own mint** (specialty_mint class; recursive
   self-application — the credibility floor);
   (ii) **SUEZ POC FULL KIT** (engagement class; Commit 4 target);
   (iii) **I82 P1 capability registry mint** (canonical_csv_mint class;
   Commit 3 target).
2. Two consecutive subsequent tranches (next 2 commits in scope) emit
   `synthesis_complete == true` with zero FAIL-severity findings.
3. Validator FAIL promotion ratified by operator-explicit decision
   (`D-IH-86-EA` successor row, e.g., `D-IH-86-EF`-shape).
4. SYN-04 / SYN-05 / SYN-08 remain at FAIL ramp permanently (mandatory-
   citation dimensions; missing citation always fails).
5. SYN-01 / SYN-02 / SYN-03 / SYN-06 / SYN-09 / SYN-10 remain at WARN
   forever (judgement-class completeness dimensions).
6. SYN-07 (atomicity) remains at FAIL ramp permanently (atomicity is
   binary; non-atomic tranches are not meaningful tranches under the
   doctrine).

The recursive self-application requirement is the credibility floor:
if the discipline can't be applied to its own mint, it can't be
applied to engagement work either.

## Self-discipline rules for agents

When closing an in-scope tranche:

1. **Classify the tranche-class BEFORE drafting any tranche-charter
   frontmatter.** Resolve via inline-ratify if ambiguous (e.g., is the
   I82 P1 capability registry a `canonical_csv_mint` only, or also a
   `specialty_mint` for the 12th specialty maturation? Answer at I82
   P1: `canonical_csv_mint`; the 12th specialty maturation is a
   separate forward-charter tranche).
2. **Run `scripts/synthesis_before_tranche_check.py --check-charter
   <path>` BEFORE drafting the tranche's UAT verdict line OR the
   master-roadmap §"Closure criteria" table.** The synthesis sweep is
   the design-layer pre-flight; UAT verdict + closure criteria are
   the post-commit signals. Doing them in the wrong order means
   discovering missing scope after committing.
3. **Compute findings count before posting the `AskQuestion` batch.**
   ≤ 10 fits one batch; 11-20 splits into 2 batches; > 20 triggers
   the tranche-split bandwidth-recovery pattern.
4. **For every `scope-extend` disposition, file a forward-pointer.**
   Either an OPS_REGISTER row with a named owner + ETA, OR a candidate-
   shaped tracker file under `docs/wip/planning/_trackers/`, OR an
   `_candidates/` file when the extension is initiative-sized.
5. **For every `scope-narrow` disposition, name what was removed.**
   The synthesis report's SYN-07 finding row records the narrowing
   explicitly so the next coordinator can find the deferred scope.
6. **For every `escalate-to-blocker-tracker` disposition, mint the
   tracker file.** Follow the shape in
   `akos-conflict-surfacing-and-blocker-trackers.mdc` §"Blocker-
   tracker file shape".
7. **Update operator-scratchpad before the tranche's commit.** The
   tranche's summary, decision IDs, synthesis findings disposition,
   and forward-pointers MUST land in
   `docs/wip/intelligence/operator-scratchpad.md` OR the
   initiative-coordinator scratchpad before the tranche's atomic
   commit lands.

